                                                            <div id="faq-24-2" class="collapse" data-bs-parent="#faq-24">
                                                                <div class="accordion-content">
                                                                    <p>There are a number of different types of bonds, from corporate bonds issued by individual companies, to municipal bonds that are typically issued to pay for a specific project, such as improvements to schools, to government Treasuries which fund the Federal government. At their heart they are all the same, they are all debt instruments. So which are best to trade? Rather than considering the source of the bond it is helpful to consider the ranking instead. There are three major bond ranking agencies, Standard & Poor’s, Moody’s, and Fitch. They all use a similar ranking method and the higher a bond is ranked, the safer it is. However lower ranked bonds are often better for trading as investors can be willing to pay more as they chase the yield.</p>
